    "recap_headline": "University of Oklahoma Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HAMMOND, La.\n\u2014 No. 8 Oklahoma fell at Southeastern Louisiana Tuesday night by a final of 3-0.\nIt was the first time the Sooners (17-4, 2-1 SEC) have been shut out this season and it was the team's second-lowest hit total on the year with four.\nA scoreless game through three innings, Oklahoma led off the fourth inning with consecutive hits from\nJaxon Willits\nand\nDeiten Lachance\nbut a double play ended the threat.\nThe Lions (12-9, 4-2 SLC) took the lead in the home half of the fourth on a single to first base before a solo home run in the fifth extended the lead to 2-0.\nThe Sooners threatened again in the seventh with a pair of base hits before another double play kept OU scoreless. SLU would add an insurance run in the bottom of the eighth on an error to bring the final to 3-0.\nOklahoma used six pitchers on the night with starting RHP\nMichael Catalano\ntaking his second loss of the season, going 3.2 innings and striking out three while allowing one run on three hits. OU pitching escaped numerous jams on the night, leaving eight SLU baserunners on base.\nFour Sooners combined for OU's four hits on the night.\nPitchers of Record\nWin: Levi Shaffer (1-0)\nLoss:\nMichael Catalano\n(1-2)\nSave: Triston Todorowski (1)\nStatistical Snapshot\nDeiten Lachance\n| 1-for-3, 1 BB\nNolan Stevens\n| 1-for-3\nConnor Larkin\n| 1-for-3\nJaxon Willits\n| 1-for-4\nMichael Catalano\n| 3.2 IP, 3 H, 1 R, 1 ER, 0 BB, 3 K\nTrent Collier\n| 1.1 IP, 2 H, 1 R, 1 ER, 0 BB, 1 K\nNotes\nOU dropped to 17-4 on the season and 0-1 on the road. Tuesday night was OU's first true road game of the season.\nIt was the first time OU has been shut out on the season. The last time the Sooners were shut out was April 3, 2025 at the hands of No. 7 LSU in Norman (0-2).\nOU snapped its streak of an extra-base hit in every game of the season. Prior to Tuesday, the Sooners had recorded at least one extra-base hit in every contest.\nThe Sooner pitching staff struck out just six on Tuesday, the second-lowest strikeout total by the staff in a game this year.\nUp Next\nOU will swing down to Baton Rouge for the second weekend of SEC play, meeting defending national champion LSU for a Thursday-Saturday series. First pitch for the opener on Thursday is slated for 7 p.m. CT on ESPNU.\nFor updates and more information on Oklahoma baseball, follow the Sooners on X and Instagram (\n@OU_Baseball\n) and like\nOklahoma Baseball\non Facebook."
